#: ../../Flocculator.rst:5
msgid "Flocculator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Flocculator.rst:7
msgid "Design information for the AguaClara flocculator is available in the `Flocculation Design chapter of The Physics of Water Treatment Design <https://aguaclara.github.io/Textbook/Flocculation/Floc_Design.html>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Flocculator.rst:11
msgid "Purpose and Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Flocculator.rst:13
msgid "The flocculator causes particles suspended in the water to collide and agglomerate to form larger aggregates called flocs. These flocs have enough weight to settle easily in the clarifier. The gentle mixing of water with coagulant in the flocculator causes collisions between particles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Flocculator.rst:15
msgid "This flocculator is a series of channels with sheets or baffles that direct the flow of water in a serpentine path. As the water goes around the end of a baffle the flow first contracts and then expands. This turbulent expansion causes fluid deformation and ultimately promotes collisions between particles."
msgstr ""

